          <p style="font-size: 1.1em; color: #ccc;">Welcome to The Fake T-Shrt Company demo data generator! This guide will help you generate and explore realistic synthetic log data.</p>

          <hr style="border-color: #444; margin: 30px 0;"/>

          <h2 style="color: #5CC05C;">1. Generate Demo Data</h2>
          <p>Navigate to the <code style="background: #333; padding: 2px 6px; border-radius: 3px;">bin/</code> directory and run the TUI generator:</p>
          <pre style="background: #1a1a1a; padding: 15px; border-radius: 5px; overflow-x: auto;">
cd $SPLUNK_HOME/etc/apps/TA-FAKE-TSHRT/bin
python3 tui_generate.py</pre>
          <p>Or use the command line:</p>
          <pre style="background: #1a1a1a; padding: 15px; border-radius: 5px; overflow-x: auto;">
# Generate all sources with default settings (14 days, exfil scenario)
python3 main_generate.py --all

# High-volume demo (31 days, all scenarios)
python3 main_generate.py --all --days=31 --scenarios=all

# Specific sources only
python3 main_generate.py --sources=asa,entraid,aws --scenarios=exfil</pre>

          <hr style="border-color: #444; margin: 30px 0;"/>

